{"parentUuid":"dec97bae-3292-472d-9eab-9ef3ac0bc71e","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a056046afd74f4258","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcsYWjiqLGb8r2un4Ppoe","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_018XRUGNzBCuqSosniLmUXPb","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\.pipeline\\surface-delta.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7263,"cache_read_input_tokens":27822,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7263,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcsYWik3mWaf5uVQszZLD","attributionAgent":"security","type":"assistant","uuid":"317ecc03-d9db-48af-ba0e-fd6e6c7b3a8d","timestamp":"2026-07-10T01:55:05.796Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"317ecc03-d9db-48af-ba0e-fd6e6c7b3a8d","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"97f8e502-2809-4fbe-ae25-bfe99bbaf354","agentId":"a056046afd74f4258","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018XRUGNzBCuqSosniLmUXPb","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Attack-surface delta — quota administration (GET/DELETE /v1/quotas)\n2\t\n3\tBest-effort hint for the security stage; reconciled against the actual diff, not authoritative.\n4\t\n5\t## New entry points\n6\t\n7\t- `GET /v1/quotas` — `src/api/routes/quotas.py:59` (`list_quotas_endpoint`). Admin-scoped read of\n8\t  the caller's own tenant's full quota list. No request body/query/path parameter.\n9\t- `DELETE /v1/quotas` — `src/api/routes/quotas.py:68` (`delete_quota_endpoint`). Admin-scoped\n10\t  removal of one `(customer_id, metric)` cap, identified by query parameters\n11\t  (`customer_id`, `metric`). 204 on success, 404 if absent.\n12\t\n13\tBoth reuse the existing `_require_admin_and_throttled` dependency (`src/api/routes/quotas.py:26`)\n14\tverbatim — no new auth path, scope, or dependency chain.\n15\t\n16\t## New trust boundaries\n17\t\n18\tNone. No outbound third-party call, no new subprocess/exec, no new SSRF-capable fetch. Both new\n19\troutes only read/write the existing `quotas` table over the existing `app <-> RDS` boundary\n20\talready used by `PUT /v1/quotas`.\n21\t\n22\t## New data flows / sinks\n23\t\n24\t- `SELECT customer_id, metric, limit_per_window FROM quotas WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id ORDER BY\n25\t  customer_id, metric` — `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py::list_quotas` (parameterized `text()`,\n26\t  no string interpolation).\n27\t- `DELETE FROM quotas WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id AND customer_id = :customer_id AND metric =\n28\t  :metric RETURNING customer_id` — `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py::delete_quota` (parameterized\n29\t  `text()`).\n30\t- No new table, no new stored field. Both queries operate on the pre-existing `quotas` table\n31\t  (migration `0003`), which already carries the `quotas_tenant_isolation` FORCE RLS policy.\n32\t- **Stored-field classification (unchanged, no new field):** `customer_id` / `metric` /\n33\t  `limit_per_window` were already classified **non-sensitive operational config** at rest under\n34\t  RDS SSE (storage-level) in the metric-quotas plan. This feature stores no new field — it only\n35\t  reads (GET) and removes (DELETE) existing rows — so no field-level KDF/KMS applies here; the\n36\t  `data_protection_waiver` in `.pipeline/acceptance.md` frontmatter documents this explicitly for\n37\t  the reconciliation.\n38\t- New log event: `quota.delete` (INFO) — `src/services/quota_service.py::delete_tenant_quota`,\n39\t  emitted via the existing structlog facade (`src/logging`), which auto-redacts `customer_id`.\n40\t\n41\t## New privilege / authz surface\n42\t\n43\t- Both new routes are authenticated + admin-scope-gated (`scope == 'admin'`), identical to the\n44\t  existing `PUT /v1/quotas`. No new scope value, no privilege widening beyond what `PUT` already\n45\t  grants an admin key.\n46\t- DELETE is a net-new **destructive** capability (removing a cap re-enables unlimited usage for\n47\t  that `(customer_id, metric)` until a new `PUT`) — mitigated by the same admin-scope gate + tenant\n48\t  isolation (`api_key_id` filter + FORCE RLS) already covering `PUT`/GET. This is the STRIDE\n49\t  Elevation-of-Privilege / IDOR-BOLA row the plan calls out (AC8 proves cross-tenant DELETE is\n50\t  invisible, matching zero rows -> 404).\n51\t\n52\t## Other changes\n53\t\n54\t- `src/api/middleware.py` — added `\"DELETE\"` to `CORSMiddleware.allow_methods`. No live-control\n55\t  effect (empty origin allowlist, server-to-server API); completeness only, matching the plan.\n56\t"}]},"uuid":"456b39a6-ad99-48e2-a8df-2ab9dfefd42e","timestamp":"2026-07-10T01:55:05.817Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"317ecc03-d9db-48af-ba0e-fd6e6c7b3a8d","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"456b39a6-ad99-48e2-a8df-2ab9dfefd42e","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a056046afd74f4258","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcsYWjiqLGb8r2un4Ppoe","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01W9exqFu9pBTMXUYpC7fJJZ","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\api\\routes\\quotas.py"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7263,"cache_read_input_tokens":27822,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7263,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcsYWik3mWaf5uVQszZLD","attributionAgent":"security","type":"assistant","uuid":"6dfc0daa-172e-4faf-99b6-97c367ae59dc","timestamp":"2026-07-10T01:55:06.292Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"6dfc0daa-172e-4faf-99b6-97c367ae59dc","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"97f8e502-2809-4fbe-ae25-bfe99bbaf354","agentId":"a056046afd74f4258","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01W9exqFu9pBTMXUYpC7fJJZ","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"`/v1/quotas` — admin-scoped create-or-replace (`PUT`), list (`GET`), and\n2\tremove (`DELETE`) of a per-customer, per-metric usage cap.\n3\t\n4\tEdge behavior (security headers, CORS, body-size guard, Tier-1 throttle) is\n5\tinherited from the middleware stack; every route on this router wires\n6\tauth -> Tier-2 throttle -> admin-scope check -> schema validation -> service,\n7\tmirroring the `events`/`usage` routes' sibling `_require_authenticated_and_throttled`\n8\tpattern (kept per-route, not shared, per the existing convention). All three\n9\tverbs depend on the same `_require_admin_and_throttled` chain — GET/DELETE\n10\treuse it verbatim rather than introducing a new scope or auth path.\n11\t\"\"\"\n12\t\n13\tfrom typing import Annotated\n14\t\n15\tfrom fastapi import APIRouter, Depends, HTTPException, Query, Request, Response, status\n16\t\n17\tfrom src.api.schemas.quotas import QuotaDeleteParams, QuotaPutRequest, QuotaResponse\n18\tfrom src.auth import require_api_key\n19\tfrom src.auth.api_key import AuthenticatedPrincipal\n20\tfrom src.auth.rate_limit import enforce_tier2_rate_limit\n21\tfrom src.logging import get_logger\n22\tfrom src.services.quota_service import (\n23\t    delete_tenant_quota,\n24\t    list_tenant_quotas,\n25\t    to_response,\n26\t    upsert_tenant_quota,\n27\t)\n28\t\n29\trouter = APIRouter(tags=[\"quotas\"])\n30\tlogger = get_logger(service=\"meterly\")\n31\t\n32\t_ADMIN_SCOPE = \"admin\"\n33\t\n34\t\n35\tasync def _require_admin_and_throttled(\n36\t    request: Request, principal: AuthenticatedPrincipal = Depends(require_api_key)\n37\t) -> AuthenticatedPrincipal:\n38\t    \"\"\"Compose auth, then the Tier-2 per-key throttle, then the admin-scope\n39\t    gate, in that order — mirrors `src/api/routes/events.py`'s dependency\n40\t    chain, extended with the function-level authorization check this route\n41\t    alone requires (ASVS 8.2.1).\n42\t    \"\"\"\n43\t    await enforce_tier2_rate_limit(request, principal)\n44\t    if principal.scope != _ADMIN_SCOPE:\n45\t        logger.warning(\n46\t            \"quota.forbidden\",\n47\t            userId=principal.api_key_id,\n48\t            action=\"deny\",\n49\t            reason=\"insufficient_scope\",\n50\t        )\n51\t        raise HTTPException(status_code=status.HTTP_403_FORBIDDEN, detail=\"admin scope required\")\n52\t    return principal\n53\t\n54\t\n55\t@router.put(\"/v1/quotas\", response_model=QuotaResponse)\n56\tasync def put_quota(\n57\t    payload: QuotaPutRequest,\n58\t    response: Response,\n59\t    principal: AuthenticatedPrincipal = Depends(_require_admin_and_throttled),\n60\t) -> QuotaResponse:\n61\t    \"\"\"Create or replace the cap for `(customer_id, metric)` under the\n62\t    caller's own tenant — 201 on create, 200 on replace.\"\"\"\n63\t    outcome = await upsert_tenant_quota(principal, payload)\n64\t    response.status_code = outcome.http_status\n65\t    return to_response(outcome)\n66\t\n67\t\n68\t@router.get(\"/v1/quotas\", response_model=list[QuotaResponse])\n69\tasync def list_quotas_endpoint(\n70\t    principal: AuthenticatedPrincipal = Depends(_require_admin_and_throttled),\n71\t) -> list[QuotaResponse]:\n72\t    \"\"\"Return the caller's own tenant's full, unpaginated quota list,\n73\t    deterministically ordered by `(customer_id, metric)`. An empty tenant\n74\t    gets `200 []`, never a 404.\"\"\"\n75\t    return await list_tenant_quotas(principal)\n76\t\n77\t\n78\t@router.delete(\"/v1/quotas\", status_code=status.HTTP_204_NO_CONTENT)\n79\tasync def delete_quota_endpoint(\n80\t    params: Annotated[QuotaDeleteParams, Query()],\n81\t    principal: AuthenticatedPrincipal = Depends(_require_admin_and_throttled),\n82\t) -> Response:\n83\t    \"\"\"Remove the cap for `(customer_id, metric)` under the caller's own\n84\t    tenant — 204 on success, 404 if no such quota exists in this tenant\n85\t    (explicit, not silently idempotent).\"\"\"\n86\t    await delete_tenant_quota(principal, params)\n87\t    return Response(status_code=status.HTTP_204_NO_CONTENT)\n88\t"}]},"uuid":"f3095c8f-5333-4605-806e-b69788a3feef","timestamp":"2026-07-10T01:55:06.310Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"6dfc0daa-172e-4faf-99b6-97c367ae59dc","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"f3095c8f-5333-4605-806e-b69788a3feef","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a056046afd74f4258","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcsYWjiqLGb8r2un4Ppoe","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_015hpVJyGghMLqnTDyYYxATp","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\api\\schemas\\quotas.py"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7263,"cache_read_input_tokens":27822,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7263,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcsYWik3mWaf5uVQszZLD","attributionAgent":"security","type":"assistant","uuid":"1979220b-e8c8-482f-b5e4-df1e2abd3e7b","timestamp":"2026-07-10T01:55:07.207Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"1979220b-e8c8-482f-b5e4-df1e2abd3e7b","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"97f8e502-2809-4fbe-ae25-bfe99bbaf354","agentId":"a056046afd74f4258","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015hpVJyGghMLqnTDyYYxATp","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"Validation contract for `PUT /v1/quotas`.\n2\t\n3\t`customer_id`/`metric` reuse the exact anchored allowlists `src/api/schemas/events.py`\n4\talready validates against (the same identifiers, same sinks) — kept as separate\n5\t`constr` instances here rather than a cross-module import so this schema stays a\n6\tself-contained boundary contract (plan's validation-contract table). `api_key_id`\n7\tand `scope` are deliberately absent: the server sets `api_key_id` from the\n8\tauthenticated principal and never accepts a client-supplied `scope`, which is\n9\tthe mass-assignment defense against writing another tenant's cap or\n10\tself-elevating privilege (ASVS 15.3.3, threat T3/E2 in the plan's STRIDE model).\n11\t\"\"\"\n12\t\n13\tfrom pydantic import BaseModel, ConfigDict, conint, constr\n14\t\n15\tCustomerId = constr(pattern=r\"^[A-Za-z0-9_.:-]{1,128}$\")\n16\tMetric = constr(pattern=r\"^[A-Za-z0-9_.:-]{1,64}$\")\n17\t# BIGINT-safe upper bound: guards against an absurd/overflowing value reaching\n18\t# the BIGINT column or the R+Q>L comparison (plan's DoS row on limit_per_window).\n19\tLimitPerWindow = conint(ge=1, le=10**15)\n20\t\n21\t\n22\tclass QuotaPutRequest(BaseModel):\n23\t    \"\"\"The client-supplied body of `PUT /v1/quotas`.\n24\t\n25\t    `extra='forbid'` rejects any unknown field outright, including a\n26\t    client-supplied `api_key_id` or `scope` — the create-or-replace identity\n27\t    is exactly `(customer_id, metric)`, resolved against the authenticated\n28\t    principal's own `api_key_id` by the service layer, never the request body.\n29\t    \"\"\"\n30\t\n31\t    model_config = ConfigDict(extra=\"forbid\")\n32\t\n33\t    customer_id: CustomerId\n34\t    metric: Metric\n35\t    limit_per_window: LimitPerWindow\n36\t\n37\t\n38\tclass QuotaResponse(BaseModel):\n39\t    \"\"\"The minimal response field set for a quota (ASVS 15.3.1) — echoes only\n40\t    what the caller supplied, never the full `quotas` row (`api_key_id`,\n41\t    `created_at`, `updated_at` stay internal).\"\"\"\n42\t\n43\t    model_config = ConfigDict(extra=\"forbid\")\n44\t\n45\t    customer_id: str\n46\t    metric: str\n47\t    limit_per_window: int\n48\t\n49\t\n50\tclass QuotaDeleteParams(BaseModel):\n51\t    \"\"\"The two required query parameters of `DELETE /v1/quotas`, reusing the\n52\t    exact same anchored `CustomerId`/`Metric` allowlists `QuotaPutRequest`\n53\t    validates against — same identifiers, same sinks, same rejection\n54\t    behavior (422). `extra='forbid'` rejects any unknown query param\n55\t    (including a client-supplied `api_key_id`), the mass-assignment defense\n56\t    that keeps the delete target's tenant resolved only from the\n57\t    authenticated principal (ASVS 15.3.3).\n58\t    \"\"\"\n59\t\n60\t    model_config = ConfigDict(extra=\"forbid\")\n61\t\n62\t    customer_id: CustomerId\n63\t    metric: Metric\n64\t"}]},"uuid":"6cc8cf0b-7786-4f71-8bf0-d149d1ee9870","timestamp":"2026-07-10T01:55:07.227Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"1979220b-e8c8-482f-b5e4-df1e2abd3e7b","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"6cc8cf0b-7786-4f71-8bf0-d149d1ee9870","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a056046afd74f4258","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcsYWjiqLGb8r2un4Ppoe","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Xfd5nZmbJjSBwu7SrWibnn","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\repositories\\quotas_repo.py"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7263,"cache_read_input_tokens":27822,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7263,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcsYWik3mWaf5uVQszZLD","attributionAgent":"security","type":"assistant","uuid":"9fdee6d6-5637-491c-9c6a-fde6db4a75a7","timestamp":"2026-07-10T01:55:07.734Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"9fdee6d6-5637-491c-9c6a-fde6db4a75a7","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"97f8e502-2809-4fbe-ae25-bfe99bbaf354","agentId":"a056046afd74f4258","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Xfd5nZmbJjSBwu7SrWibnn","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"Repository for `quotas` — the per-tenant, per-customer, per-metric usage\n2\tcap `upsert_quota` writes, and the atomic read-and-decide\n3\t`read_tenant_quota_state_locked` `POST /v1/events` consults.\n4\t\n5\tEvery query here is scoped by the authenticated `api_key_id` first (the\n6\trow-level-security invariant from `code-standards`); the PostgreSQL RLS\n7\tpolicy `quotas_tenant_isolation` is the backstop if this scoping were ever\n8\tmissing from a query.\n9\t\"\"\"\n10\t\n11\tfrom dataclasses import dataclass\n12\tfrom datetime import datetime\n13\tfrom decimal import Decimal\n14\t\n15\tfrom sqlalchemy import text\n16\tfrom sqlalchemy.ext.asyncio import AsyncSession\n17\t\n18\t\n19\t@dataclass(frozen=True)\n20\tclass QuotaRecord:\n21\t    \"\"\"The stored/echoed shape of a `quotas` row plus whether this call\n22\t    created it (`inserted`) or replaced an existing cap.\"\"\"\n23\t\n24\t    customer_id: str\n25\t    metric: str\n26\t    limit_per_window: int\n27\t    inserted: bool\n28\t\n29\t\n30\t@dataclass(frozen=True)\n31\tclass QuotaState:\n32\t    \"\"\"The result of the atomic read-and-decide: the configured cap and the\n33\t    current-window rollup total, read together under `FOR UPDATE OF q`.\"\"\"\n34\t\n35\t    limit_per_window: int\n36\t    current_total: Decimal\n37\t\n38\t\n39\t@dataclass(frozen=True)\n40\tclass QuotaListItem:\n41\t    \"\"\"One row of `GET /v1/quotas`'s listing — the minimal, public quota shape.\"\"\"\n42\t\n43\t    customer_id: str\n44\t    metric: str\n45\t    limit_per_window: int\n46\t\n47\t\n48\tasync def upsert_quota(\n49\t    session: AsyncSession,\n50\t    *,\n51\t    api_key_id: int,\n52\t    customer_id: str,\n53\t    metric: str,\n54\t    limit_per_window: int,\n55\t) -> QuotaRecord:\n56\t    \"\"\"Create-or-replace the cap for `(api_key_id, customer_id, metric)` in\n57\t    one statement, reporting whether this call inserted a new row.\n58\t\n59\t    `RETURNING (xmax = 0) AS inserted` is the idiom that distinguishes a\n60\t    fresh `INSERT` from an `ON CONFLICT DO UPDATE` in a single round-trip: a\n61\t    freshly inserted row's `xmax` (the deleting-transaction marker) is still\n62\t    zero, while an updated row's `xmax` is set by the `UPDATE` — so the\n63\t    service can map `inserted -> 201` else `200` without a second read-before-\n64\t    write query or the TOCTOU race that would introduce.\n65\t    \"\"\"\n66\t    result = await session.execute(\n67\t        text(\n68\t            \"\"\"\n69\t            INSERT INTO quotas (api_key_id, customer_id, metric, limit_per_window, updated_at)\n70\t            VALUES (:api_key_id, :customer_id, :metric, :limit_per_window, now())\n71\t            ON CONFLICT (api_key_id, customer_id, metric) DO UPDATE SET\n72\t                limit_per_window = EXCLUDED.limit_per_window,\n73\t                updated_at = now()\n74\t            RETURNING customer_id, metric, limit_per_window, (xmax = 0) AS inserted\n75\t            \"\"\"\n76\t        ),\n77\t        {\n78\t            \"api_key_id\": api_key_id,\n79\t            \"customer_id\": customer_id,\n80\t            \"metric\": metric,\n81\t            \"limit_per_window\": limit_per_window,\n82\t        },\n83\t    )\n84\t    row = result.mappings().one()\n85\t    return QuotaRecord(\n86\t        customer_id=row[\"customer_id\"],\n87\t        metric=row[\"metric\"],\n88\t        limit_per_window=row[\"limit_per_window\"],\n89\t        inserted=row[\"inserted\"],\n90\t    )\n91\t\n92\t\n93\tasync def read_tenant_quota_state_locked(\n94\t    session: AsyncSession,\n95\t    *,\n96\t    api_key_id: int,\n97\t    customer_id: str,\n98\t    metric: str,\n99\t    window_start: datetime,\n100\t) -> QuotaState | None:\n101\t    \"\"\"Lock the quota row, then read the current-window rollup total fresh —\n102\t    the atomic check-then-decide mechanism `POST /v1/events` uses to enforce\n103\t    `R + Q <= L` without a TOCTOU race (plan §\"The atomic read-and-decide\").\n104\t\n105\t    Returns None when no quota row matches `(api_key_id, customer_id,\n106\t    metric)` — the caller treats this as unlimited and takes no lock at all\n107\t    (the common, zero-contention path).\n108\t\n109\t    **Two round-trips, deliberately, not one combined `LEFT JOIN ... FOR\n110\t    UPDATE` statement.** `FOR UPDATE` only guarantees a fresh re-read of the\n111\t    *locked* row itself (via PostgreSQL's `EvalPlanQual` recheck) when a\n112\t    waiter unblocks after the lock holder commits — it does **not** force a\n113\t    fresh snapshot for other tables read in the same statement, including a\n114\t    `LEFT JOIN`. A waiter that queued for the lock before the holder\n115\t    committed would evaluate that join against its own original (pre-wait)\n116\t    snapshot and read a stale `total_quantity`, silently breaking strict\n117\t    enforcement under real concurrency (verified empirically: a single\n118\t    combined statement let every concurrent waiter read the same stale\n119\t    total and all get admitted). Issuing the `usage_rollup` read as its own\n120\t    statement *after* the lock is acquired gives it a fresh per-statement\n121\t    READ COMMITTED snapshot, which does include everything the previous lock\n122\t    holder just committed — this is what actually makes `current_total`\n123\t    accurate for every waiter, not just the first, uncontended caller.\n124\t    \"\"\"\n125\t    lock_result = await session.execute(\n126\t        text(\n127\t            \"\"\"\n128\t            SELECT limit_per_window\n129\t            FROM quotas\n130\t            WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id AND customer_id = :customer_id AND metric = :metric\n131\t            FOR UPDATE\n132\t            \"\"\"\n133\t        ),\n134\t        {\"api_key_id\": api_key_id, \"customer_id\": customer_id, \"metric\": metric},\n135\t    )\n136\t    lock_row = lock_result.mappings().first()\n137\t    if lock_row is None:\n138\t        return None\n139\t\n140\t    rollup_result = await session.execute(\n141\t        text(\n142\t            \"\"\"\n143\t            SELECT total_quantity\n144\t            FROM usage_rollup\n145\t            WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id AND customer_id = :customer_id\n146\t              AND metric = :metric AND window_start = :window_start\n147\t            \"\"\"\n148\t        ),\n149\t        {\n150\t            \"api_key_id\": api_key_id,\n151\t            \"customer_id\": customer_id,\n152\t            \"metric\": metric,\n153\t            \"window_start\": window_start,\n154\t        },\n155\t    )\n156\t    rollup_row = rollup_result.mappings().first()\n157\t    current_total = rollup_row[\"total_quantity\"] if rollup_row is not None else Decimal(0)\n158\t    return QuotaState(limit_per_window=lock_row[\"limit_per_window\"], current_total=Decimal(current_total))\n159\t\n160\t\n161\tasync def list_quotas(session: AsyncSession, *, api_key_id: int) -> list[QuotaListItem]:\n162\t    \"\"\"Return every quota row for the caller's own tenant, ordered by\n163\t    `(customer_id, metric)` for a deterministic, repeatable listing.\n164\t\n165\t    The `ORDER BY` matches the leading columns of the table's primary key\n166\t    `(api_key_id, customer_id, metric)`, so the sort is index-friendly on top\n167\t    of the already-scoped index scan (plan §\"deterministic ORDER BY\").\n168\t    \"\"\"\n169\t    result = await session.execute(\n170\t        text(\n171\t            \"\"\"\n172\t            SELECT customer_id, metric, limit_per_window\n173\t            FROM quotas\n174\t            WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id\n175\t            ORDER BY customer_id, metric\n176\t            \"\"\"\n177\t        ),\n178\t        {\"api_key_id\": api_key_id},\n179\t    )\n180\t    return [\n181\t        QuotaListItem(\n182\t            customer_id=row[\"customer_id\"],\n183\t            metric=row[\"metric\"],\n184\t            limit_per_window=row[\"limit_per_window\"],\n185\t        )\n186\t        for row in result.mappings().all()\n187\t    ]\n188\t\n189\t\n190\tasync def delete_quota(\n191\t    session: AsyncSession, *, api_key_id: int, customer_id: str, metric: str\n192\t) -> bool:\n193\t    \"\"\"Remove the cap for `(api_key_id, customer_id, metric)`, returning\n194\t    whether a row actually matched and was removed.\n195\t\n196\t    `RETURNING customer_id` on a single-statement, parameterized `DELETE` is\n197\t    what lets the service distinguish \"removed\" from \"nothing there to\n198\t    remove\" without a separate existence check (avoiding a TOCTOU gap\n199\t    between check and delete). The explicit `api_key_id` filter is the\n200\t    primary tenant-confinement control; `quotas_tenant_isolation` FORCE RLS\n201\t    (migration `0003`) is the backstop — a cross-tenant call matches zero\n202\t    rows here, which the service maps to 404 (plan §\"Tenant confinement is\n203\t    structural, not a special case\").\n204\t    \"\"\"\n205\t    result = await session.execute(\n206\t        text(\n207\t            \"\"\"\n208\t            DELETE FROM quotas\n209\t            WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id AND customer_id = :customer_id AND metric = :metric\n210\t            RETURNING customer_id\n211\t            \"\"\"\n212\t        ),\n213\t        {\"api_key_id\": api_key_id, \"customer_id\": customer_id, \"metric\": metric},\n214\t    )\n215\t    return result.mappings().first() is not None\n216\t"}]},"uuid":"dff7acdf-3c9d-4e8b-aa14-0d064a512e6a","timestamp":"2026-07-10T01:55:07.762Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"9fdee6d6-5637-491c-9c6a-fde6db4a75a7","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"dff7acdf-3c9d-4e8b-aa14-0d064a512e6a","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a056046afd74f4258","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcsYWjiqLGb8r2un4Ppoe","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Ae6gaZo1YcEdxSBpTkh9xW","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\services\\quota_service.py"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7263,"cache_read_input_tokens":27822,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7263,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcsYWik3mWaf5uVQszZLD","attributionAgent":"security","type":"assistant","uuid":"b67e581c-e5eb-4f11-aa44-9ceca9e5a71d","timestamp":"2026-07-10T01:55:08.734Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"b67e581c-e5eb-4f11-aa44-9ceca9e5a71d","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"97f8e502-2809-4fbe-ae25-bfe99bbaf354","agentId":"a056046afd74f4258","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Ae6gaZo1YcEdxSBpTkh9xW","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"Service for `/v1/quotas` — the admin-scoped upsert (`PUT`), list (`GET`),\n2\tand remove (`DELETE`) operations.\n3\t\n4\tEach entry point orchestrates one transaction per request: the `xmax` upsert\n5\tin `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py` reports create-vs-replace in a single\n6\tround-trip for `PUT`; `GET` opens a read-only scoped transaction for the\n7\tordered listing; `DELETE` maps \"no row matched\" to a 404 rather than a\n8\tsilent success (plan §\"DELETE — remove one cap, explicitly\").\n9\t\"\"\"\n10\t\n11\tfrom dataclasses import dataclass\n12\t\n13\tfrom fastapi import HTTPException, status\n14\t\n15\tfrom src.api.schemas.quotas import QuotaDeleteParams, QuotaPutRequest, QuotaResponse\n16\tfrom src.auth.api_key import AuthenticatedPrincipal\n17\tfrom src.db.session import scoped_transaction\n18\tfrom src.logging import get_logger\n19\tfrom src.repositories.quotas_repo import delete_quota, list_quotas, upsert_quota\n20\t\n21\tlogger = get_logger(service=\"meterly\")\n22\t\n23\t\n24\t@dataclass(frozen=True)\n25\tclass QuotaUpsertOutcome:\n26\t    \"\"\"The result of processing a `PUT /v1/quotas` request: the stored quota\n27\t    and the HTTP status the route should return (201 create, 200 replace).\"\"\"\n28\t\n29\t    customer_id: str\n30\t    metric: str\n31\t    limit_per_window: int\n32\t    http_status: int\n33\t\n34\t\n35\tasync def upsert_tenant_quota(\n36\t    principal: AuthenticatedPrincipal, payload: QuotaPutRequest\n37\t) -> QuotaUpsertOutcome:\n38\t    \"\"\"Create-or-replace the cap for `(customer_id, metric)` under the\n39\t    authenticated principal's own `api_key_id` — the server, never the\n40\t    client, sets `api_key_id`, which is the mass-assignment protection\n41\t    (ASVS 15.3.3) against writing another tenant's cap.\n42\t    \"\"\"\n43\t    async with scoped_transaction(principal.api_key_id) as session:\n44\t        record = await upsert_quota(\n45\t            session,\n46\t            api_key_id=principal.api_key_id,\n47\t            customer_id=payload.customer_id,\n48\t            metric=payload.metric,\n49\t            limit_per_window=payload.limit_per_window,\n50\t        )\n51\t\n52\t    action = \"create\" if record.inserted else \"replace\"\n53\t    logger.info(\n54\t        \"quota.upsert\",\n55\t        userId=principal.api_key_id,\n56\t        action=action,\n57\t        customer_id=record.customer_id,\n58\t        metric=record.metric,\n59\t        limit_per_window=record.limit_per_window,\n60\t    )\n61\t    return QuotaUpsertOutcome(\n62\t        customer_id=record.customer_id,\n63\t        metric=record.metric,\n64\t        limit_per_window=record.limit_per_window,\n65\t        http_status=201 if record.inserted else 200,\n66\t    )\n67\t\n68\t\n69\tdef to_response(outcome: QuotaUpsertOutcome) -> QuotaResponse:\n70\t    \"\"\"Map the service outcome to the minimal public response shape (ASVS 15.3.1).\"\"\"\n71\t    return QuotaResponse(\n72\t        customer_id=outcome.customer_id,\n73\t        metric=outcome.metric,\n74\t        limit_per_window=outcome.limit_per_window,\n75\t    )\n76\t\n77\t\n78\tasync def list_tenant_quotas(principal: AuthenticatedPrincipal) -> list[QuotaResponse]:\n79\t    \"\"\"Return the caller's own tenant's full, deterministically ordered quota\n80\t    list — an empty tenant gets an empty list, never a 404 (plan §\"Empty set\n81\t    -> 200 [], never 404\"). Deliberately not logged as a business event (open\n82\t    question 1, resolved default): a plain read of the caller's own\n83\t    configuration, mirroring `GET /v1/usage`.\n84\t    \"\"\"\n85\t    async with scoped_transaction(principal.api_key_id) as session:\n86\t        rows = await list_quotas(session, api_key_id=principal.api_key_id)\n87\t\n88\t    return [\n89\t        QuotaResponse(customer_id=row.customer_id, metric=row.metric, limit_per_window=row.limit_per_window)\n90\t        for row in rows\n91\t    ]\n92\t\n93\t\n94\tasync def delete_tenant_quota(\n95\t    principal: AuthenticatedPrincipal, params: QuotaDeleteParams\n96\t) -> None:\n97\t    \"\"\"Remove the cap for `(customer_id, metric)` under the caller's own\n98\t    tenant, raising 404 if no such quota exists (explicit, not silently\n99\t    idempotent — plan §\"Why 404-on-absent, not idempotent-204\").\n100\t\n101\t    A cross-tenant delete attempt matches zero rows (the `api_key_id` filter\n102\t    + FORCE RLS backstop), which is indistinguishable from a truly-absent\n103\t    quota — the intended BOLA-safe behavior (threat E2).\n104\t    \"\"\"\n105\t    async with scoped_transaction(principal.api_key_id) as session:\n106\t        removed = await delete_quota(\n107\t            session,\n108\t            api_key_id=principal.api_key_id,\n109\t            customer_id=params.customer_id,\n110\t            metric=params.metric,\n111\t        )\n112\t\n113\t    if not removed:\n114\t        raise HTTPException(status_code=status.HTTP_404_NOT_FOUND, detail=\"quota not found\")\n115\t\n116\t    logger.info(\n117\t        \"quota.delete\",\n118\t        userId=principal.api_key_id,\n119\t        action=\"delete\",\n120\t        customer_id=params.customer_id,\n121\t        metric=params.metric,\n122\t    )\n123\t"}]},"uuid":"47e904d4-63ce-4d66-b81b-21d83bb4c28b","timestamp":"2026-07-10T01:55:08.748Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"b67e581c-e5eb-4f11-aa44-9ceca9e5a71d","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"47e904d4-63ce-4d66-b81b-21d83bb4c28b","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a056046afd74f4258","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcsYWjiqLGb8r2un4Ppoe","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_015x1HE1nyHqjpoMWVR9XErh","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\api\\middleware.py"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7263,"cache_read_input_tokens":27822,"output_tokens":786,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7263},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":786,"cache_read_input_tokens":27822,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7263,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7263,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcsYWik3mWaf5uVQszZLD","attributionAgent":"security","type":"assistant","uuid":"40b532b9-fe60-4e0c-aeff-ce2502babb09","timestamp":"2026-07-10T01:55:08.906Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
{"parentUuid":"40b532b9-fe60-4e0c-aeff-ce2502babb09","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"97f8e502-2809-4fbe-ae25-bfe99bbaf354","agentId":"a056046afd74f4258","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015x1HE1nyHqjpoMWVR9XErh","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"Centralized edge middleware — security headers, CORS, the body-size guard,\n2\tand the Tier-1 (pre-auth, IP+route-keyed) throttle.\n3\t\n4\tRegistered once at app construction (`src/main.py`) in the order\n5\t`api-edge-conventions` specifies: request-id/trace, security headers, CORS,\n6\tbody-size guard, Tier-1 throttle, auth guard, Tier-2 throttle, handler. No\n7\troute re-declares any of this — a new endpoint inherits it by being mounted\n8\ton the app.\n9\t\"\"\"\n10\t\n11\tfrom collections.abc import Awaitable, Callable\n12\t\n13\tfrom fastapi import FastAPI, status\n14\tfrom fastapi.middleware.cors import CORSMiddleware\n15\tfrom starlette.middleware.base import BaseHTTPMiddleware\n16\tfrom starlette.requests import Request\n17\tfrom starlette.responses import JSONResponse, Response\n18\t\n19\tfrom src.auth.rate_limit import get_tier1_limiter\n20\tfrom src.config.settings import Settings\n21\tfrom src.logging import get_logger\n22\t\n23\tlogger = get_logger(service=\"meterly\")\n24\t\n25\t_SECURITY_HEADERS = {\n26\t    \"Strict-Transport-Security\": \"max-age=63072000; includeSubDomains\",\n27\t    \"X-Content-Type-Options\": \"nosniff\",\n28\t    \"Content-Security-Policy\": \"default-src 'none'\",\n29\t    \"X-Frame-Options\": \"DENY\",\n30\t    \"Referrer-Policy\": \"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\",\n31\t    \"Permissions-Policy\": \"geolocation=(), camera=(), microphone=()\",\n32\t}\n33\t\n34\t\n35\tclass SecurityHeadersMiddleware(BaseHTTPMiddleware):\n36\t    \"\"\"Sets a fixed set of security headers on every response, including error responses.\"\"\"\n37\t\n38\t    async def dispatch(\n39\t        self, request: Request, call_next: Callable[[Request], Awaitable[Response]]\n40\t    ) -> Response:\n41\t        \"\"\"Run the request, then stamp the security header set onto the response.\"\"\"\n42\t        response = await call_next(request)\n43\t        for header_name, header_value in _SECURITY_HEADERS.items():\n44\t            response.headers[header_name] = header_value\n45\t        if request.url.path.startswith(\"/v1/usage\"):\n46\t            # Usage totals are billing-adjacent personal-scoped data — never cache\n47\t            # them client-side or in an intermediary (ASVS 14.3.2).\n48\t            response.headers[\"Cache-Control\"] = \"no-store\"\n49\t        return response\n50\t\n51\t\n52\tclass BodySizeLimitMiddleware(BaseHTTPMiddleware):\n53\t    \"\"\"Rejects a request whose `Content-Length` exceeds the configured cap with 413.\n54\t\n55\t    These payloads are tiny by design (a handful of scalar fields); an\n56\t    unbounded body is a cheap denial-of-service vector worth rejecting before\n57\t    it reaches any parsing.\n58\t    \"\"\"\n59\t\n60\t    def __init__(self, app: FastAPI, *, max_body_size_bytes: int) -> None:\n61\t        super().__init__(app)\n62\t        self._max_body_size_bytes = max_body_size_bytes\n63\t\n64\t    async def dispatch(\n65\t        self, request: Request, call_next: Callable[[Request], Awaitable[Response]]\n66\t    ) -> Response:\n67\t        \"\"\"Check `Content-Length` before invoking the rest of the stack.\"\"\"\n68\t        content_length = request.headers.get(\"content-length\")\n69\t        if content_length is not None:\n70\t            try:\n71\t                if int(content_length) > self._max_body_size_bytes:\n72\t                    return JSONResponse(\n73\t                        status_code=status.HTTP_413_REQUEST_ENTITY_TOO_LARGE,\n74\t                        content={\n75\t                            \"error\": {\n76\t                                \"code\": \"payload_too_large\",\n77\t                                \"message\": \"request body exceeds the maximum allowed size\",\n78\t                                \"requestId\": getattr(request.state, \"request_id\", \"unknown\"),\n79\t                            }\n80\t                        },\n81\t                    )\n82\t            except ValueError:\n83\t                pass  # malformed Content-Length falls through to normal request handling/validation\n84\t        return await call_next(request)\n85\t\n86\t\n87\t# Paths exempt from the Tier-1 Redis throttle: the liveness probe must return\n88\t# 200 with *zero* dependencies (no DB, no Redis) — it is the smoke check's and\n89\t# the build-fallback's only signal, and gating it on Redis would make a cache\n90\t# outage look like a total application outage (plan §\"health split\").\n91\t_TIER1_EXEMPT_PATHS = frozenset({\"/health\"})\n92\t\n93\t\n94\tclass Tier1EdgeThrottleMiddleware(BaseHTTPMiddleware):\n95\t    \"\"\"Pre-auth, IP+route-keyed Redis token bucket — sheds an anonymous flood\n96\t    before the request can spend an Argon2id verification (mitigates D1/D3).\n97\t    \"\"\"\n98\t\n99\t    def __init__(self, app: FastAPI, *, capacity: int, refill_rate_per_second: float) -> None:\n100\t        super().__init__(app)\n101\t        self._capacity = capacity\n102\t        self._refill_rate_per_second = refill_rate_per_second\n103\t\n104\t    async def dispatch(\n105\t        self, request: Request, call_next: Callable[[Request], Awaitable[Response]]\n106\t    ) -> Response:\n107\t        \"\"\"Consume one token from the `client_ip:route` bucket before proceeding.\n108\t\n109\t        Fails **open** (allows the request, logs a warning) on a Redis\n110\t        connection error rather than 500ing every request — an unreachable\n111\t        cache degrading to \"temporarily unlimited\" is preferable to a full\n112\t        outage of the ingest path; Tier-2's per-key bucket and the underlying\n113\t        DB constraints remain the durable protections either way.\n114\t        \"\"\"\n115\t        if request.url.path in _TIER1_EXEMPT_PATHS:\n116\t            return await call_next(request)\n117\t\n118\t        client_ip = request.client.host if request.client else \"unknown\"\n119\t        bucket_identity = f\"{client_ip}:{request.url.path}\"\n120\t        try:\n121\t            decision = await get_tier1_limiter().check(\n122\t                bucket_identity,\n123\t                capacity=self._capacity,\n124\t                refill_rate_per_second=self._refill_rate_per_second,\n125\t            )\n126\t        except Exception:  # noqa: BLE001 - a Redis outage must not take down the whole API\n127\t            logger.warning(\"ratelimit.backend_unavailable\", endpoint=request.url.path, tier=\"tier1\")\n128\t            return await call_next(request)\n129\t\n130\t        if not decision.allowed:\n131\t            logger.warning(\n132\t                \"ratelimit.exceeded\",\n133\t                userId=None,\n134\t                action=\"deny\",\n135\t                endpoint=request.url.path,\n136\t                reason=\"tier1_bucket_exhausted\",\n137\t            )\n138\t            return JSONResponse(\n139\t                status_code=status.HTTP_429_TOO_MANY_REQUESTS,\n140\t                content={\n141\t                    \"error\": {\n142\t                        \"code\": \"rate_limited\",\n143\t                        \"message\": \"too many requests\",\n144\t                        \"requestId\": getattr(request.state, \"request_id\", \"unknown\"),\n145\t                    }\n146\t                },\n147\t                headers={\"Retry-After\": str(max(1, int(decision.retry_after_seconds) or 1))},\n148\t            )\n149\t        return await call_next(request)\n150\t\n151\t\n152\tdef configure_cors(app: FastAPI, settings: Settings) -> None:\n153\t    \"\"\"Register the CORS middleware with an explicit origin allowlist from config.\n154\t\n155\t    Defaults to an empty allowlist (this is a server-to-server API, not a\n156\t    browser client) rather than `*` — `api-edge-conventions` forbids\n157\t    reflecting an arbitrary origin.\n158\t    \"\"\"\n159\t    app.add_middleware(\n160\t        CORSMiddleware,\n161\t        allow_origins=list(settings.cors_allowed_origins),\n162\t        allow_credentials=False,\n163\t        allow_methods=[\"GET\", \"POST\", \"PUT\", \"DELETE\"],\n164\t        allow_headers=[\"Authorization\", \"Content-Type\", \"Idempotency-Key\"],\n165\t    )\n166\t"}]},"uuid":"3eecdebd-cf7b-480b-bf77-d2f6f918024d","timestamp":"2026-07-10T01:55:08.935Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"40b532b9-fe60-4e0c-aeff-ce2502babb09","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
