{"parentUuid":"c80dd9ab-4e44-43d7-879e-e8244bb505a2","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a056046afd74f4258","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Ccsbr5tf2q7hLx56xKzYj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Reconciliation passes: `scan_reconciled: true`, no count mismatches, no scope gaps. All gate-read fields validate (`status: clean`, `critical_count: 0`, `asvs.reconciled: true`, `input_surface.reconciled: true`, `data_surface.reconciled: true`).\n\n## Summary\n\n**Tools:** Semgrep (auto + p/secrets + p/owasp-top-ten + p/python), Gitleaks, OSV, Trivy fs, lockfile-check, asvs-sast, ast-grep (advisory), SBOM. **Scope:** diff vs `ef3fb3f`. **Result: 0 critical / 2 warnings / 1 fixed — status `clean`, scan_reconciled true.**\n\nThe quota-admin feature (GET/DELETE `/v1/quotas`) is well-hardened — Semgrep, Trivy, asvs-sast, and ast-grep all clean on the change set; parameterized SQL, anchored allowlist validation, admin-scope gate, per-tenant `api_key_id` filtering with FORCE RLS backstop (verified owner-owns-table so FORCE is efficacy-required and present), minimal response projection, and a fail-closed generic-500 boundary. All 10 STRIDE mechanisms present + efficacy-correct; **AC18 ASVS reconciliation complete** (chapters V1/V2/V4/V6/V8/V12/V13/V14/V16, L1/L2 + in-scope L3 V8.2.x met, no unwaived gaps); input/data-surface both reconciled; no new un-modeled attack surface.\n\n**Fixed (1):** `.gitignore` lacked a `.terraform/` entry, so `git ls-files --others` was pulling ~108 MB of vendored HashiCorp provider `.exe` binaries into the change set — added `.terraform/` (kept the committable `infra/.terraform.lock.hcl`); the change set dropped from 8 untracked entries to 2. File: `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\.gitignore`.\n\n**Warnings (2, non-blocking):**\n1. **OSV CVE-2025-71176** in `pytest 8.3.4` (dev/test-only), CVSS ~6.8 Medium — **below the ≥7.0 gate floor**. Action: bump `pytest >= 9.0.3` (manifest not modified per policy; human decides).\n2. **Tier-1 throttle IP-keying behind the ALB** (`src/api/middleware.py:118`) with no `--proxy-headers` trust configured — **pre-existing, out of this diff's scope**; the effective admin-route control is the topology-independent per-`api_key_id` Tier-2 bucket (`rate_limit.py:153`, proven by AC12). Noted for backlog.\n\n**Out of scope:** Gitleaks' 128 hits are all in gitignored `.venv/`, `.pipeline/archive/`, prior-feature docs, and two prior-feature test fixtures — zero in any quota change-set file.\n\nArtifacts written: `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\.pipeline\\security-report.md` and `...\\.pipeline\\security-status.json` (raw scans in `.pipeline/semgrep.json`, `osv.json`, `trivy-fs.json`, `gitleaks.json`, `sbom.cdx.json`)."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":641,"cache_creation_input_tokens":595,"cache_read_input_tokens":116941,"output_tokens":1772,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":595},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":641,"output_tokens":1772,"cache_read_input_tokens":116941,"cache_creation_input_tokens":595,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":595,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccsbr4tsxzNRKzeexZJab","attributionAgent":"security","type":"assistant","uuid":"93b7f2e0-53fa-40d6-8115-73f35e498b0b","timestamp":"2026-07-10T02:39:04.883Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
